on linux machine pip for python 2 , python3 pip3 :
 - sudo apt-get install python-pip/python3-pip
 - pip/pip3 help
 - pip/pip3 search Pympler
 - pip/pip3 install Pympler
 - pip/pip3 list
 - pip/pip3 uninstall Pympler
 - pip list -o
 - pip install -U <package name>
 ==
 - pip freeze (for example : pip freeze > requirements.txt)
 - pip install -r requirements.txt (install packages from file)

 ==
 Bonus, upgrade all :
 pip freeze --local | grep -v '^\-e' | cut -d = -f 1  | xargs -n1 pip install -U
